Statistics South Africa  publishes
January consumer-price inflation data at 10 a.m. on its website.  Inflation probably accelerated to an annual 3.7 percent
last month from 3.5 percent in December, according to the median
estimate of 20 economists surveyed by Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alastair Reed in Johannesburg at 
